latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So here it is… My 2021! It’s been nothing short of a crazy jam packed, exhilarating fun filled year but wouldn’t have it any other way. It’s always challenging putting together a collection of images from the whole year but fulfilling looking back at all the moments that have been captured for all my amazing clients. So thank you to all my clients, who have trusted and chosen me to document their special day. 

For all my 2022/23 clients I can’t wait to get to know you better and be part of your wedding. 

Have a fantastic Christmas and New Years and stay safe!

latestIgtvVideos.title: TWENTY TWENTY
latestIgtvVideos.caption: As challenging as this year has been I have still been fortunate enough to document a handful of amazing stories in 2020. It has been tough for everybody, all my amazing couples and everyone in our industry. However, we have to make the most of the situation we are in and hope and pray that 2021 we will all come back stronger and better and celebrate these amazing events in style. Here’s a little snapshot of my 2020 ;)

latestPosts.caption:
Ever since Priya & Nayan contacted me last year and told me about their venue I had been looking forward to shooting their wedding all year. 

A destination wedding vibe in the UK. From the stunning cliff top views of the sea to the magnificent castle it was the perfect backdrop. 

It had rained the morning of the wedding and we were on edge a bit as it would have been such a shame to move the wedding indoors. Luckily just as the Jaan started the sun made an appearance… blue skies and stunning views of the sea. @sagarvyasevents being the prefect hype man everyone involved had a great time. Once Priya made her entrance the two embraced each other like they hadn’t seen each other forever. the whole ceremony was filled with love and laughter. 

After the ceremony we managed to get down to the beach which was a trek and hard work with the heat but Priya was a trooper who made it down with her lengha. Quite a work out!

Priya & Nayan have been so much fun to work with and so just so happy they chose to have me as their photographer. Will be posting more from the reception shortly!

latestPosts.caption:
After all the excitement of the pre-wedding celebrations, the big day finally arrived! We kicked things off bright and early with Sonal’s emotional bridal reveal on the balcony with her family — a truly unforgettable moment and one of the highlights of the day.
The jaan arrived in style, with dhol beats and dancing as everyone made their way to the mandap set on the hotel grounds near the beach. 

Sonal made a stunning entrance, lovingly escorted by her sister, and the ceremony, beautifully led by Ravi Shastri, was filled with warmth and joy.
We wrapped things up with some fun portraits by the beach — the perfect ending to a beautiful wedding.

latestPosts.caption:
Jaymin & Hetika had their Indian Wedding yesterday at Old Thorns. We had been looking forward to this day for some time especially after their amazing Civil & Reception last week. 

We started the morning off with getting some family portraits of Hetika’s family when another family decided to photo bomb which was hilarious. Shortly after we kicked the Jaan  down the drive all the way to the venue. The ceremony was conducted beautifully by @shrihemangbhai which set the tone for peace and tranquility. It was an emotional day with lots of tears of joy and happiness. 

After the Ceremony we managed to get on to the course and got some lovely portraits before giving Hetika a lovely send off. Thank you once again for having me to be your photographer and with you both all the happiness in the world!

Instead of traditional catering, these two brought in a pizza truck — such a fun and personal touch! Then it was time to turn up the energy for the Reception:
Otis set the vibe with his sax,
SNK’s canapés kept everyone fuelled, and
Ash brought the house down with all the bangers!

The dance performances were and the whole night was full of joy, energy, and celebration.

Can’t wait for the Indian wedding next week! Let’s go again!

What an incredible day celebrating Misha & Ashwin’s wedding!  It was extra special for me, having captured Misha’s sister’s wedding 7 years ago.
The day was packed from start to finish, a heartfelt Civil ceremony in the morning, a beautiful Indian wedding led by the amazing Ram Pandey, and an unforgettable Reception to close it all off.

One of my personal highlights was the first look before the Civil—so full of raw, genuine emotions. 
 Ashwin made a stylish entrance in a classic Porsche for the jaan, The ceremony was conducted by Ram Pandey giving Misha a beautiful send off. Will be posting more from the Reception later!
